<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>7.3 Liter Diesel Engine Service (1991) - CONNECTING RODS, PISTONS AND RINGS - CONNECTING RODS, PISTONS AND
        RINGS (Reconditioning)
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>CONNECTING RODS, PISTONS AND RINGS (Reconditioning)</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="0">
            <title>PISTON DISASSEMBLY</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove piston rings using piston ring expander tool.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the connecting rod from the piston pin assembly as follows:</para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Using a suitable pliers
                        <emph type="bold"></emph>(
                        <emph type="bold">Figure
                            <hotlnk document="e435_96.xml" xrefid="ef4350517">5.17</hotlnk>
                        </emph>
                        ), remove the piston pin retaining rings from each end of the pin.
                    </para>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Insert piston in any suitable vise (piston O.D. must be protected from damage) and drive
                    piston pin (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk document="e435_96.xml" xrefid="ef4350518">5.18</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ) from piston and rod assembly using a nylon rod or brass drift and a soft hammer.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Separate connecting rod from piston.</para>
                <specpara>
                    <important>
                        <para>MAKE SURE PARTS ARE MARKED SO THEY ARE REINSTALLED IN THEIR RESPECTIVE CYLINDERS, UNLESS
                            DEFECTIVE.
                        </para>
                    </important>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
